@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam maxMessageSize 250
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam NoteBorderColor #F9A825

title Agent → Supabase: Data Flow & Transformations

participant "OS APIs\n(psutil, ping3\nspeedtest, socket)" as OS
participant "DataCollector\ncollector.py" as DC
participant "run_with_user()\nmain.py" as Main
participant "UploadQueue\nqueue.py" as Q
participant "Flask /api/ingest\napi.py" as API
participant "Database ORM\ndb_operations.py" as DB
participant "Supabase\nPostgreSQL" as PG

== Desktop Network (Main Thread, every 30s) ==

OS -> DC : raw OS values
note over OS
  psutil.net_connections() → list of sconn objects
  psutil.net_io_counters() → snetio named tuple
  ping3.ping("1.1.1.1") → float (seconds) or None
  speedtest.download() → int (bits/sec)
  socket.getsockname() → ("192.168.x.x", port)
end note

DC -> Main : NetworkMetrics dataclass
note over DC
  @dataclass NetworkMetrics:
    ping: float              # ms
    packet_loss_percent: float
    download_speed_mbps: float
    upload_speed_mbps: float
    ip_address: str
    test_method: str
    tcp_connections: Optional[int]
    bytes_sent: Optional[int]
    bytes_recv: Optional[int]
end note

Main -> Q : enqueue(payload)
note over Main
  Plain Python dict (fields selected from NetworkMetrics):
  {
    "sample_type":    "desktop_network",
    "device_id":      "647f...",         ← str(UUID)
    "ts":             "2026-03-11T10:00:00+00:00",
    "latency_ms":     12.4,
    "packet_loss_pct": 0.0,
    "down_mbps":      94.2,
    "up_mbps":        22.1,
    "test_method":    "Official Speedtest CLI",
    "ip":             "192.168.1.5",
    "tcp_connections": 42,
    "bytes_sent":     1024000,
    "bytes_recv":     4096000
  }
end note

== UploadQueue: dict → file → HTTP ==

Q -> Q : json.dumps(payload, separators=(",",":"))
note over Q
  Compact JSON string — no spaces:
  {"sample_type":"desktop_network","device_id":"647f...","ts":"2026-03-11T10:00:00+00:00","latency_ms":12.4,...}

  Written as one line to agent_queue.jsonl:
  line1\n   ← desktop_network payload
  line2\n   ← cloud_latency payload  (if queued)
  line3\n   ← mobile_wifi payload    (if queued)
end note

Q -> API : HTTP POST /api/ingest
note over Q
  urllib.request — UTF-8 encoded bytes:
  POST http://200.69.13.70:5017/api/ingest
  Content-Type: application/json

  body: b'{"sample_type":"desktop_network",...}'
end note

== Flask: bytes → DB insert ==

API -> API : request.get_json()
note over API
  Flask deserializes body back to Python dict.
  Routes on sample_type:

  "desktop_network" → db.insert_desktop_network_sample()
  "cloud_latency"   → db.insert_cloud_latency_sample()
  "mobile_wifi"     → db.insert_mobile_wifi_sample()
end note

API -> DB : insert_desktop_network_sample(device_id, data)
note over API
  Dict fields are unpacked as kwargs:
  db.insert_desktop_network_sample(
    device_id = UUID("647f..."),
    ts        = datetime.fromisoformat("2026-03-11T10:00:00+00:00"),
    latency_ms = 12.4,
    down_mbps  = 94.2,
    ...
  )
end note

DB -> DB : Sample(ORM object)
note over DB
  SQLAlchemy ORM model instantiated:
  Sample(
    device_id    = UUID object,
    sample_type  = "desktop_network",
    ts           = datetime object,
    latency_ms   = 12.4,
    down_mbps    = 94.2,
    up_mbps      = 22.1,
    tcp_connections = 42,
    bytes_sent   = 1024000,
    bytes_recv   = 4096000,
    latency_eu_ms = None,    ← NULL for non-cloud rows
    wifi_rssi_dbm = None     ← NULL for non-mobile rows
  )
  session.add(sample)
  session.commit()
end note

DB -> PG : INSERT INTO samples (...)
note over PG
  PostgreSQL row:
  ┌────┬───────────┬─────────────────┬────────────┬───────────┬──────────┬──────┐
  │ id │ device_id │ sample_type     │ latency_ms │ down_mbps │ eu_ms    │ rssi │
  ├────┼───────────┼─────────────────┼────────────┼───────────┼──────────┼──────┤
  │ 42 │ 647f...   │ desktop_network │ 12.4       │ 94.2      │ NULL     │ NULL │
  └────┴───────────┴─────────────────┴────────────┴───────────┴──────────┴──────┘
end note

== Cloud Latency (cloud-latency thread, every 300s) ==

OS -> DC : Globalping API JSON response
note over OS
  HTTP GET https://api.globalping.io/v1/measurements/{id}
  {
    "status": "finished",
    "results": [
      { "probe": { "country": "DE" },
        "result": { "stats": { "avg": 14.2 } } },
      { "probe": { "country": "US" },
        "result": { "stats": { "avg": 89.1 } } },
      { "probe": { "country": "CN" },
        "result": { "stats": { "avg": 201.4 } } }
    ]
  }
end note

DC -> Main : CloudLatencyResult dataclass
note over DC
  @dataclass CloudLatencyResult:
    latency_eu_ms:   14.2
    latency_us_ms:   89.1
    latency_asia_ms: 201.4
end note

Main -> Q : enqueue(payload)
note over Main
  {
