== Mobile WiFi (mobile-connector thread, every 30s) ==

OS -> DC : Raw SQL rows from mobile Supabase DB
note over OS
  SELECT wifi_rssi_dbm, link_speed_mbps,
         is_connected, ts, created_at
  FROM wifi_samples
  WHERE user_id = ? AND created_at > ?

  Returns: list of SQLAlchemy Row tuples
  e.g. (-67.0, 144.0, True, datetime(...), datetime(...))
end note

DC -> Main : list[dict]
note over DC
  get_new_samples() converts each Row to dict:
  [
    {
      "wifi_rssi_dbm":   -67.0,
      "link_speed_mbps": 144.0,
      "is_connected":    True,
      "ts":              datetime(2026, 3, 11, 9, 58, 0),
      "created_at":      datetime(2026, 3, 11, 9, 58, 1)
    },
    ...
  ]
end note

Main -> Q : enqueue(payload) per sample
note over Main
  {
    "sample_type":     "mobile_wifi",
    "device_id":       "uuid-of-mobile-device",
    "ts":              "2026-03-11T09:58:00",  ← ts.isoformat()
    "wifi_rssi_dbm":   -67.0,
    "link_speed_mbps": 144.0,
    "is_connected":    true
  }
end note

DB -> PG : INSERT INTO samples (...)
note over PG
  ┌────┬───────────┬─────────────┬────────────┬──────────┬──────────────┬──────────────┐
  │ id │ device_id │ sample_type │ latency_ms │ eu_ms    │ wifi_rssi    │ link_speed   │
  ├────┼───────────┼─────────────┼────────────┼──────────┼──────────────┼──────────────┤
  │ 44 │ mobile... │ mobile_wifi │ NULL       │ NULL     │ -67.0        │ 144.0        │
  └────┴───────────┴─────────────┴────────────┴──────────┴──────────────┴──────────────┘
end note

@enduml
